post_text:
Good evening,

Unfortunately, the power is still out in both school buildings and the downed power pole and lines have not been touched by George O. Barr Elementary. For that reason, school is cancelled tomorrow.

Once I have a better idea when power will be restored, a plan will be put in place for return to school and device/hotspot pickup. My understanding is that is could be a few more days until power is back on in many areas. As soon as information is available, I will send a message to all families.

Take care,

Dr. VandeWiele

post_text:
Good evening,

The absolute last thing that I want to do is call off the first day of school, but that is exactly what I need to do this evening. We do not currently have power in either school building. In addition, a power pole snapped, branches are down, and power lines are in the street by George O. Barr Elementary. This is a very unsafe situation, particularly for any students that walk to school.

Many individuals are currently without power, cell service, or WiFi, so if you get this message, please pass this information on to other families in our district.

At this point, all I can do is shake my head and hope that the power is back on some time tomorrow so we can have school on Wednesday.

I will keep you informed.

Terri VandeWiele

Superintendent

post_text:
Preschool Information

The first day for preschool students will be during our Hand in Hand Preschool Orientation. You and your child should plan to attend to meet the teachers and pick up learning packets. For students in group A, please meet in the cafeteria on Wednesday, August 12th at 7:50 for the AM session or 10:20 for the PM session. For students in group B, please meet in the cafeteria on Thursday, August 13th at 7:50 for the AM session and 10:20 for the PM session. For remote only students, you may choose one of the times above. This orientation will last about 30 minutes, after which you will take your child home with you. This orientation does not include Ms. Rachel’s morning class.
If you do not know what group your child is assigned to, please call the school at 792-0639.

post_text:
ATTENTION PRESCHOOL FAMILIES
You are invited to our Hand in Hand Preschool Orientation. Your child will meet the teachers and we will have learning packets ready for you to pick up during this time. For students in group A, please meet in the cafeteria on Wednesday, August 12th at 7:50 for the AM session or 10:20 for the PM session. For students in group B, please meet in the cafeteria on Thursday, August 13th at 7:50 for the AM session and 10:20 for the PM session. For remote only students, you may choose one of the times above.
If you do not know what group your child is assigned to, please call the school at 792-0639.

post_text:
Last night, the Board of Education approved the amended school calendar for the upcoming school year. The major changes include:

1. Addition of 5 remote learning planning days to provide employees with the necessary time needed for professional development and planning.

2. The Illinois legislature mandated that Election Day, which is November 3rd, be a non-attendance day. We will make up this day on February 15th. As of today, this will only be in effect this school year.

post_text:
HAND IN HAND PRESCHOOL SCREENING AT GEORGE O. BARR

The Silvis School District #34 has scheduled Preschool Screening for the 2020-2021 school year for Wednesday July 8th, 2020. This state-funded program is for children ages 3-5 who live in the Silvis School District and are not eligible for kindergarten. The program is a half-day session at George O. Barr with a certified teacher and aide. Children who live on the bus route will also have transportation to and from school. Children must be screened to be considered for the program. If you have a three or four year child or know of someone in the Silvis School District who does, please email Mrs. Staples for a screening appointment at gail.staples@silvis34.com. Screenings will be held at George O. Barr Elementary School, 1305 5th Avenue, Silvis.

SUMMER MEAL PROGRAM through the Two Rivers YMCA's Nourish Youth Nutrition Collaborative

Families will be able to pick up 2 breakfasts and 2 lunches for each child in their home on Mondays, Wednesdays, and Fridays from 10:30 am - noon. Pick up locations will be the Y's Spirit, Mind, & Body Center (1811 53rd Street Moline) and the Boys & Girls Club of the Mississippi Valley (406 7th Street Moline).

https://www.tworiversymca.org/blog/summer-meal-program

If you have questions, please contact Jeff Cornelius at jcornelius@ymcatr.org

The Silvis Main Street has scheduled a Graduate Parade for the UTHS Seniors of 2020 who live in Silvis. It will take place on Wednesday June 3rd @ 6:30pm.

Graduates will be lined up with their cap and gowns (6ft apart) outside George O Barr School...as family, friends, and the community will drive by and show their support.

Please see this event hosted by Silvis Main Street, and if you have any questions you can ask there...

post_text:
HAND IN HAND PRESCHOOL SCREENING AT GEORGE O. BARR

The Silvis School District #34 has scheduled Preschool Screening for the 2020-2021 school year for Wednesday July 8th, 2020. This state-funded program is for children ages 3-5 who live in the Silvis School District and are not eligible for kindergarten. The program is a half-day session at George O. Barr with a certified teacher and aide. Children who live on the bus route will also have transportation to and from school. Children must be screened to be considered for the program. If you have a three or four year child or know of someone in the Silvis School District who does, please email Mrs. Staples for a screening appointment at gail.staples@silvis34.com. Screenings will be held at George O. Barr Elementary School, 1305 5th Avenue, Silvis.

post_text:
NEJH - is anyone having trouble with their Chromebook since the logins were changed from .net to .com?

Here is what you shoud try, according to Mrs. Sensabaugh

1. When students open their Chromebook, there should be a picture with their name and a spot for their username.

2. Next to their name is an arrow. Click the arrow.

3. There should be an option to remove or delete the user. Choose this option.

4. Have the student add a user.

5. They will then log in with their email ending in .com. Their password should be the same.

This should solve the problem. If you are still having problems, please let me know. Thank you for your patience during this transition.

We hope you are all doing well and miss you! Have a great day!

https://www.facebook.com/532450660222659/posts/1842645962536449/?d=n
shared_text:
St. Mark's Anglican Church
April 23 at 10:19 PM ·

What a glorious day. St Mark’s, in conjunction with RiverBend Food Bank, the Tri-City Jewish Center and Silvis School District gave fresh produce to 420 cars and fed 1720 people. This brings our 3 week total to 5200 people fed. Praise be to God!

Terri VandeWiele

Silvis Main Street
April 1 at 8:17 PM ·

We have SUCH A GREAT community!!! I just received a call from Father Jason at St. Marks Church and they will be handing out fresh produce tomorrow, Thursday April 2nd at 2pm!! There is NO charge, NO questions asked, NO ID’s have to be shown, they will have it already bagged up, AND you will stay in your car!!! In a time of need...our community is really stepping up!! PLEASE stop by St. Marks Church 1550 7th ave Silvis and pick up a bag😊😊

post_text:
Dear Silvis School District Parents,

This afternoon, the governor cancelled school in all Illinois districts, starting Tuesday, March 17. With consultation of local authorities, as well as other superintendents, we have made the decision to cancel classes on Monday, March 16 as well. Both school buildings will be open on Monday, March 16, from 8:00 am until 10:00 am, in order for parents to pick up medications or other essential items. I ask that you refrain from coming into the buildings, unless it is absolutely necessary.

These are unprecedented times. Thank you for your patience as we navigate these uncharted water. Please read the attached letter for more information on the closure, including plans being made to provide meals and educational opportunities to students during the time period that school is closed.

Wishing you all the best during the challenging days ahead.

Terri VandeWiele

Terri VandeWiele

Good evening Silvis families.

We are still down two bus drivers and need to utilize adjusted pick up and drop off times until further notice. The good news is that we are close to having sub drivers in place, so the situation should be rectified soon. We are so sorry for any problems this may cause for any of our families.

All Northeast students who ride the red route will get picked up 15 minutes earlier in the morning than normal with the first stop being at 6:45am. The orange route for Northeast may be 5 minutes late and the green route should run as normal.

The morning elementary route will run as normal except the Falcon Farms route which will be picked up around 7:35am instead of 7:50. Finally, the Northeast PM Orange route will need to be dismissed a half hour early. All other PM routes at both schools should run normally. Please see the post on our Facebook page, if needed.

Thank you for your understanding.

Dr. VandeWiele

HAND IN HAND PRESCHOOL SCREENING AT GEORGE O. BARR

The Silvis School District #34 will hold screenings for its Hand In Hand Preschool program for the 2020-2021 school year on Wednesday, March 4th, Thursday, May 14th and Wednesday, July 8th, 2020. This state-funded program is for children ages 3-5 who live in the Silvis School District and are not eligible for kindergarten. The program is a half-day session at George O. Barr with a certified teacher and aide. Children who live on the bus route will also have transportation to and from school. Children must be screened to be considered for the program. If you have a three or four year old child or know of someone in the Silvis School District who does, please call Mrs. Staples for a screening appointment at 792-0639 ext. 190. If necessary, leave a phone number and your call will be returned. Screenings will be held at George O.Barr Elementary School, 1305 5th Avenue, Silvis.

post_text:
8th Grade Parents/Guardians:

It is hard to believe, but our 8th grade students are already preparing for high school! I wanted to share a few upcoming dates.
On Tuesday, February 18th, UTHS is hosting a Parent Night. The event begins at 7:00 pm. Information will be sent home with the students.
The 8th grade students will be taking a tour of UTHS on Monday, February 24th. The bus will take the students to UTHS and the school counselors from UTHS will lead the tour. The students will have their pictures taken for their school ID as well. The students will also get materials to create their class schedules for next year.
The UTHS school counselors will meet with our students individually the following week to review and collect their schedules. The official schedules will be mailed home from UTHS in May.
Please feel free to contact me with any questions.
Thank you!

Jen Caldwell
Counselor, Northeast Junior High
309-203-1300 ext 121

post_text:
Shout-out to the awesome 3rd Grade Emerging
Bilingual (EL) students who have worked so hard on their country
projects. In the 3rd curriculum, they learn about access to education
and how children in other countries have access to books and educational opportunities.
Once we studied that, we decided to do projects on each of their home
countries -- over four weeks we studied Mexico, Togo, Sudan, and Egypt
and each student got to be an expert on their country. I am so proud of them!

Mrs. Henderson, Preschool-4th Grade Emerging Bilinguals Teacher

Students are asked to bring non-perishable food items to their morning advisory class through November 8th.

Any student that donates 50 cans will have their name entered into a drawing to win a $50 Visa gift card. The advisory that brings in the most cans throughout the hunger drive will win an advisory party. Any student who brings in 5 items or $3 will earn a PE no dress pass (limit one per student).
Please help our students help UTHS!

post_text:
A message from Dr. VandeWeile regarding the Class Rank Forum at UTHS:

United Township High School is investigating a switch from the current system of honoring top students through class rank (Valedictorian/Salutatorian), to the Latin Model (Summa Cum Laude, Magna Cum Laude, Cum Laude). If a switch is made, it would be for the incoming 9th-grade class (Class of 2024).

I am passing along a press release from Dr. Morrow regarding a public input meeting being held on this proposed change. The meeting is scheduled for Monday, October 28th, at 6:00 pm in the UTHS Student Commons.

Since this proposed change would impact your student, I wanted to be sure and pass along the meeting information.

Thank you,

Dr. Terri VandeWiele
Superintendent
Silvis School District #34

Monday, October 7 through Monday, October 14: Fall Intersession

We hope you have a wonderful Fall Intersession and look forward to seeing everyone on October 15th.

Sincerely,

Dr. VandeWiele
